claim.claim-text:
18. An improved locking mechanism for a fifth wheel assembly for a tractor-trailer truck, said truck having a tractor and a trailer; the trailer having a coupling plate with a downwardly extending kingpin; the tractor having the assembly mounted thereon; the assembly having a coupling plate for coupling with the trailer coupling plate; the assembly coupling plate including a pair of rearwardly projecting ramps separated by a kingpin-receiving gap having a blind port to receive the kingpin; the improved locking mechanism comprising: 
a lever having a front end; 
a lock bar extending from the lever; 
a lock jaw retained by the lock bar in a locked position adjacent the blind port, but biased to move to an unlocked position when the lever is pivoted to move the lock bar to at least partially release the lock jaw from the lock bar, allowing the lock jaw to move; arid 
the assembly including a housing having an aperture formed therein through which a handle passes, the handle extending from adjacent the front end of the lever.

20. An improved locking mechanism for a fifth wheel assembly for a tractor-trailer truck, said truck having a tractor and a trailer; the trailer having a coupling plate with a downwardly extending kingpin; the tractor having the assembly mounted thereon; the assembly having a coupling plate for coupling with the trailer coupling plate; the assembly coupling plate including a pair of rearwardly projecting ramps separated by a kingpin-receiving gap having a blind port to receive the kingpin; the improved locking mechanism comprising: 
a lever; 
a lock bar extending from the lever; 
a C-shaped lockjaw having first and second ends retained by the lock bar in a locked position adjacent the blind port, but biased to move to an unlocked position when the lever is pivoted to move the lock bar to at least partially release the lock jaw from the lock bar, allowing the lock jaw to move; and 
the lock bar engaging the lock jaw on the first end in the locked position and on the second end in the unlocked position.
